text:
(1)
Murrsy Hulbert Avenue, north from Cross Street, ear pier 13. The view shows the area before the thoroughfare was laid out when the Foreign Trade Zone was established. The avenue runs north and south along the entire Stapleton waterfront. In the left background are warehouses of the American Dock Company, near Victory Boulevard, Tompkinsville.

June 15, 1935

P. L. Sperr

(2)
The same section of the avenue, some months later.
Note the many pits in the pavement.

October 19, 1936

P. L. Sperr
title: Richmond: Murray Hulbert Avenu - Cross Street
